From f2e9ed950d4fc922fac07f40d3c2ed8b4e96784b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: torusmini <torusmini@torusminideMac-mini.local>
Date: Wed, 3 Jun 2026 20:21:09 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Add FutureSeed and feature-diff noise to EqR

Timestamp: 2026-06-03T12:21:09Z

Implements two opt-in mechanisms for EqR: learned cross-level FutureSeed mixers and feature-difference Langevin noise sampled from a non-persistent hidden-feature ring buffer.

Defaults preserve upstream EqR behavior: future_seed_scale=0.0, noise_mode=gaussian, and no FutureSeed parameters appear in default state_dicts.

Runtime evaluation overrides now support noise_mode, feature_noise_fallback, and future_seed_scale, with validation and a warning when an old checkpoint lacks FutureSeedMixer modules.

Validation: python -m py_compile models/eqr.py evaluate.py; git diff --check; direct CPU forward smoke for default and futureseed_featurediff configs; CPU torch.compile forward smoke for futureseed_featurediff.

Experience and lesson: EqR's eval-time stochastic breadth means feature noise must maintain an online non-persistent buffer during forward, not just during training; buffer mutation is wrapped with torch compile disable to avoid Dynamo capturing stateful sampling.
